Sentencas: Decalcomania is a new method for SOFCs (solid oxide fuel cells) unit cell fabrication.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania

Sentencas: A tight and dense 5 mu m Yttria-stabilized zirconia (8YSZ) electrolyte layer on anode substrate was fabricated by the decalcomania method.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania

Sentencas: After 8YSZ as the electrolyte starting material was calcined at 1200 degrees C, the particle size was controlled by the attrition mill.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania

Sentencas: The median particle size (D50) of each 8YSZ was 39.6 mu m, 9.30 mu m, 6.35 mu m, and 3.16 mu m, respectively.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania

Sentencas: The anode substrate was coated with decalcomania papers which were made by using 8YSZ with different median particle sizes.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania

Sentencas: In order to investigate the effect of median particle sizes and sintering conditions on the electrolyte density, each sample was sintered for 2, 5 and 10 h, respectively.
Titulo: Densification and Electrochemical Properties of YSZ Electrolyte Decalcomania Paper for SOFCs by Decalcomania
